text: Châtelaudren is a former commune. It is found in the region Bretagne in the Côtes-d'Armor department in the west of France. On 1 January 2019, it was merged into the new commune of Châtelaudren-Plouagat.Arrêté préfectoral 28 September 2018 == References == Category:Former communes in Côtes-d'Armor
title: Châtelaudren
